<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-688-029  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 688 029.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Government Computer News  Dec 10 1990 v9 n26 p67(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>People.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Department of DefensePromotion of EmployeeNetwork ArchitectureEngineeringUnited States. Federal Aviation AdministrationAir Traffic ControlData Security.andO;Person:    Elliot, Ronald D. (Achievements and awards); Mollenauer, James H.andO;(Achievements and awards).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Ronald D. Elliott has been awarded the Secretary of Defense MeritoriousCivilian Service Award.andP;  Elliott is technical director of the DefenseDepartment's Intelligence Communications Architecture project.andM;Elliott received the award for his Integrated Tactical-Strategic DataNetworking (ITDN) concept, which was demonstrated last year and could be usedin the Persian Gulf crisis.andM;ITDN allows computers operating at multiple security levels to interconnectover common networks using off-the-shelf equipment and existing militarytransmission systems.andM;The assistant secretary of defense for command, control, communications andintelligence has ordered the Defense Communications Agency to devise a planfor deploying ITDN.andM;In its fiscal 1991 budget authorization report, the Senate Armed ServicesCommittee called for Integrated Services Digital Network installation at alllevels of the Defense Department and recommended its use in other agencies.andM;James H. Mollenauer, retired director of the Federal System AviationAdministration's System Research and Development Service, is one of fourrecipients of the Elmer A. Sperry Award.andP;  The award was sponsored jointly bysix professional engineering societies, including the Institute of Electricaland Electronics Engineers Inc.andM;The award recognized the four men's contributions toward the conception,design, development and delivery of the central computer complex of the FAAEn Route Air Traffic Control System, which controls all commercial aircraftin the continental United States.andP;  Also receiving the award were Claud M.andO;Davis, Richard B. Hanrahan and John F. Keeley, all employees of IBM Corp.andM;People make the federal computing community work, yet few get the recognitionthey deserve.andP;  If you know of a job change, promotion or award, send the newsto the People Desk, Government Computer News, 8601 Georgia Ave., Suite 300,Silver spring, Md.andP;  20910.andP;  Include a daytime phone number so we can confirmthe information.andO;</TEXT></DOC>